author: Brian Lloyd
title: Life | A baby was delivered on the M50 this morning
text:
It's one of those stories that'll probably become a family tradition.
"Did you know you were born on the side of a motorway by a fireman?" Early this morning, crews from Dublin Fire Brigade and an ambulance crew helped deliver a baby girl on the side of the M50.
Judging by this photo, we'd hazard a guess and say it's just past where the toll cameras heading northbound.
Fire and ambulance crews from Kilbarrack assisted the delivery of a baby girl on the M50 at 0330. #fastlanedelivery pic.twitter.com/EtEz9Z5bdC
â€” Dublin Fire Brigade (@DubFireBrigade) October 18, 2015 So, let's talk potential names for the girl.
- Emma? Like as in Emma 50?
- Ikea? Obvious one, but sure lookit.
- If it was a boy, you could call him AnaTOLLi, because of the toll bridge.
Got any ideas of your own? Let us know in the comments!
Via Twitter
